    SEE A CLEARER FUTURE with innovative goals-based investment management solutions
more  Horizon Investments provides goals-based investment management strategies to financial advisors and their clients.

advisor


investor
Horizon’s goals-based strategies are designed to provide an all-important direct link between investment strategies and the investor’s key objectives. This link enables advisors to navigate the three key stages of the investor's financial lives. Each stage demands different investment, risk mitigation and spending strategies. We call these three stages Gain, Protect and Spend. 

GAIN


PROTECT


SPEND










About Us - Horizon Investments     




Redirecting...You are now leaving the Horizon Investments website and entering the Horizon Funds website.
OK
CANCEL
 about usOverviewPhilosophyHistoryTeam

Horizon is a leading provider of modern goals-based investment management. We work in partnership with financial advisors to deliver investment strategies that align clients’ wealth with their life goals.OUR MISSIONProvide goals-based investment management strategies that will empower financial advisors to help their clients achieve their most important financial objectives throughout life.True investment success is all about meeting the most important life goals that your clients have set out for themselves, their families and even the world at large.That’s why Horizon’s approach is built on a commitment to goals-based investment management. A goals-based approach can help investors position their wealth to support the key financial results they seek throughout their lives. When your clients align their wealth with their goals, they achieve something that most people can only hope for: The financial security they need to live life on their terms.OUR DEDICATIONSuccessfully advocate on behalf of financial advisors and their critical role in helping clients achieve their most important and meaningful financial goals.Bring effective risk mitigation strategies to independent financial advisors and their clients in order to help them protect the wealth they have built.Help financial advisors build elite and highly successful businesses through our expert insights, training and consulting in all major areas of practice management.Deliver effective retirement income strategies that are built to address the challenges of historically low interest rates and rising life expectancies.Goals-Based Investment ManagementHorizon’s goals-based strategies are designed to provide an all-important direct link between investment strategies and clients’ key objectives. This link enables clients to address the three distinct stages throughout their investment lifecycle.GainClients seek to grow wealth so it can support and enhance their most important life goals.ProtectClients seek to guard wealth against catastrophic losses that could jeopardize their financial security.SpendClients seek to ensure that their wealth is there for them during what may be lengthy and active retirements.Horizon Investments helps advisors build and manage entrepreneurial advisory businesses. Our experience encompasses every aspect of owning, operating and building a financial advisory business—wealth management, financial planning, investment management, client relationship management, client acquisition, marketing, technology, staffing and succession. We offer this knowledge to our advisor clients through a comprehensive suite of education, training and consulting solutions through our experienced team of advisor consulting associates.Choose an option below to learn moreAdvisorsInvestors  Horizon Investments was founded in 1995 as an independent financial advisory firm serving individuals and families in the Columbia, South Carolina area. Since that time working directly with investors, we have expanded our mission and capabilities.Today, with headquarters in Charlotte, North Carolina, Horizon provides comprehensive investment and practice management solutions to independent financial advisors across the country. The firm was recognized in 2014 and 2016 for growth and innovation by Money Management Institute, and has received numerous industry commendations for its investment management expertise.  We know advisors because we are advisors. Everything we do at Horizon is designed to help our fellow advisors deliver a superior experience to their clients and build successful businesses. Our deep roots in the financial advisory world mean we understand the issues that financial advisors care about. The challenges that financial advisors worry about. And the resources that financial advisors must seek out to achieve success for their clients, their teams, their partners and themselves.We are a community of professionals working together in an effort to provide best-in-class financial services and superior customer service to our clients. The unique blend of professionals within our investment team provides a variety of skill sets and experience that allows us to balance quantitative diligence with qualitative wisdom.InvestmentsRobbie CannonRobbie CannonPresident + CEORobbie Cannon is the President and CEO of Horizon Investments, LLC, which specializes in active asset allocation, risk mitigation and retirement income. During his tenure, which began in 1999, Horizon has grown from a small retail RIA firm to a multi-billion dollar third-party investment management group with a national footprint of independent broker dealers and institutional clients. His career in finance began in 1994, and has encompassed various aspects of portfolio management including asset allocation, equity analysis and risk management. He graduated from Furman University and lives in Charlotte, NC.

Mr. Cannon is a national speaker on topics from asset allocation and risk management to market dynamics.Ron Saba, CFARon Saba, CFASenior Managing Director of Investment ManagementWith three decades of investment management experience, Mr. Saba he is responsible for the management of Horizon's dividend and equity portfolio strategies and also contributes bottom-up, fundamental research for the investment team. Prior to joining Horizon in 2009, Mr. Saba was Managing Partner and Chief Investment Officer of Charlotte Capital, LLC where he was lead portfolio manager for the firm’s two institutional investment products. Prior to Charlotte Capital, Mr. Saba was a Portfolio Manager with Pioneer Investments. Before Pioneer he served as a Portfolio Manager and Analyst with Heartland Advisors. Mr. Saba regularly contributes to the financial media. He has appeared on CNBC and has been featured in Barron’s magazine. Mr. Saba holds an MBA from the University of Chicago Graduate School of Business and a BS in Business Administration from The Ohio State University.Kevin Blocker, CAIAKevin Blocker, CAIAPortfolio ManagerOne of the original developers of the firm’s investment process, Mr. Blocker specializes in quantitative analysis and portfolio construction using traditional and alternative investment strategies. As a member of the firm’s Investment Committee, Mr. Blocker is responsible for screening investment opportunities and portfolio optimization.Mr. Blocker received a BA and BS in mathematics, computer science, and Spanish at Wofford College. Mr. Blocker also holds the CAIA designation. Before Horizon, Mr. Blocker played shortstop for the Colorado Rockies organization.Scott LadnerScott LadnerHead of InvestmentsMr. Ladner serves as Head of Investment Management and is the Chair of the Investment Committee for Horizon. In these capacities, he oversees all aspects of the Investment Management division for the firm.  He also provides the Investment Management division with Macro analysis and interpretation of global derivatives, credit, foreign exchange, equity, and funding markets.  His previous roles at Horizon included Head of Risk and Director of Quantitative & Alternative Strategies.Prior to Horizon, Mr. Ladner was a founder of Charlotte Global Advisors and Principal Guard, LLC. Mr. Ladner helped to launch an equity index volatility and dispersion trading unit at PEΔK6 Investments in Chicago, a proprietary listed option and volatility trading firm. Previously at First Union/Wachovia, Mr. Ladner founded and ran the $4 billion equity swap and forwards portfolio while also managing equity option and volatility portfolios. He also co-founded and managed the Risk Arbitrage and Special Situations portfolio. Mr. Ladner then managed the $300 billion notional swaption and cap/floor portion of the bank’s interest rate derivatives portfolio.Mr. Ladner received his BA in Economics and Russian Language & Literature from the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.William Breen, Ph.D.William Breen, Ph.D.Senior Product Research SpecialistDr. Breen brings the firm decades of fundamental, economic, and quantitative research with the ability to innovate his experiences with today’s current investment problems. Before Horizon, Dr. Breen was chairman and a founding director of Disciplined Investment Advisors, an equity manager with over $2 billion under management. Dr. Breen is Emeritus Professor of Finance at the Kellogg Graduate School of Management at Northwestern University, where he also was chairman of the Finance Department and head of Doctoral Studies. He has published more than 40 articles and academic papers and has co-authored several books on investment strategy, corporate finance, asset pricing, and econometric theory. He has served on the boards of The LaSalle Trust Company, Barton-Ashmann, X10ion Inc., and the Evanston Community Foundation. Dr. Breen received a Ph.D. in econometrics from Cornell University, completed graduate work at the London School of Economics as a Rotary International Fellow, and received a BA in economics and mathematics from Ripon CollegeGregory ValliereGregory ValliereChief Global StrategistGreg Valliere is the Chief Global Strategist at Horizon Investments.  With over three decades of experience following Washington for investors, Greg brings a unique perspective to Horizon -- analyzing policy and politics and their impact on the markets.After Graduating from George Washington University, Greg co-founded The Washington Forum, which linked Wall Street with Washington.  He subsequently held several positions, including Director of Research at the Charles Schwab Washington Research Group.Greg specializes in coverage of the Federal Reserve, economic policy and -- of course -- politics. He is a frequent guest on CNBC, Bloomberg TV and radio, CNN, Fox Business News and CBS radio. He is frequently quoted in The Wall Street Journal, Barrons and The New York Times.
Greg is a member of the Conference of Business Economists and holds a Series 7 license.   He and his wife Mary live in downtown DC, at the Watergate.Steven Clark, Ph.D.Steven Clark, Ph.D.Managing Director, Structured Financial SolutionsDr. Clark is an Associate Professor of Finance at UNC Charlotte where he conducts research in the areas of mathematical finance, derivative securities, asset pricing, and financial econometrics. His work at Horizon focuses on volatility forecasting models, dynamic factor models, and other quantitative methods with an emphasis toward the Quantitative investment team and toward the firm’s Risk Management suite of products. He has a Ph.D. in Mathematical Sciences (with a concentration in applied probability and stochastic modeling) and a Ph.D. in Applied Economics (with a concentration in financial economics), both from Clemson University. He has been published in numerous scholarly journals including Review of Derivatives Research, Review of Futures Markets, Journal of Risk and Insurance, and Journal of Asset Management.Calvin DeBoerCalvin DeBoerDirector of Trading and TechnologyMr. DeBoer joined Horizon Investments in December 2006. He supports the firm as Director of Trading and Technology. Mr. DeBoer supports product development at Horizon and is an integral part of the firm's software and system development efforts. Mr. DeBoer holds a BS in Finance from the University of North Carolina at Charlotte. As a student, Mr. DeBoer co-managed the Student Managed Investment Fund (SMIF), a portion of the University's endowment, and was voted top analyst by his peers.Steven AverittSteven AverittQuantitative StrategistMr. Averitt joined Horizon Investments in April 2012. He supports the firm’s quantitative research efforts including model development, testing, and validation. Previously, Mr. Averitt worked as a senior consultant and lead software engineer for Kalsi Engineering, a high technology engineering consulting firm. His expertise is in the development of proprietary engineering software products. His experience includes a broad range of software development skills including mathematical modeling, interface design, programming, integration, testing, and marketing. Mr. Averitt received his MS in Mathematical Finance from the University of North Carolina at Charlotte and his BS in Mechanical Engineering from Texas A&M University.Austin FitchAustin FitchSenior Analyst/ConsultantMr. Fitch joined Horizon Investments in January 2011. He focuses on fundamental research and supports the firm in its trading operations. He also works on product development for the firm’s consulting and retirement portfolios. Mr. Fitch holds an MBA with a concentration in Finance from the University of Tennessee and a BS in Mathematics and a BA in Finance from Wofford College.As a student, Mr. Fitch was a Fund Manager of the Haslam Torch Fund at the University of Tennessee and a Managing Partner of the R. Michael James Student-Managed Investment Fund at Wofford College.Mike Dickson, Ph.D.Mike Dickson, Ph.D.Director of Structured Financial SolutionsDr. Dickson joined Horizon Investments in March 2015. He focuses on new product development and innovation, with an emphasis on retirement income strategies. He also supports Horizon’s investment process through the development of quantitative methods and strategies.
Dr. Dickson specializes in the areas of return predictability, portfolio optimization, and factor models.  Previously, he taught undergraduate finance at UNC Charlotte and worked in financial analysis support roles at Premier, Inc., and Global Compliance. Dr. Dickson received his BS in Chemistry from Winthrop University and both an MS in Economics and Ph.D. in Finance from UNC Charlotte.LeadershipRobbie CannonRobbie CannonPresident + CEORobbie Cannon is the President and CEO of Horizon Investments, LLC, which specializes in active asset allocation, risk mitigation and retirement income. During his tenure, which began in 1999, Horizon has grown from a small retail RIA firm to a multi-billion dollar third-party investment management group with a national footprint of independent broker dealers and institutional clients. His career in finance began in 1994, and has encompassed various aspects of portfolio management including asset allocation, equity analysis and risk management. He graduated from Furman University and lives in Charlotte, NC.

Mr. Cannon is a national speaker on topics from asset allocation and risk management to market dynamics.John DrahzalJohn DrahzalHead of DistributionJohn is responsible for overseeing all aspects of the firm’s distribution strategy, including sales, marketing and strategic account management. John is a member of Horizon’s Executive Committee and will also be responsible for corporate development for the firm.

He began his career as a portfolio manager and equity analyst with Victory Asset Management where managed client portfolios and followed the consumer cyclical sector. He then joined the leadership team in helping to launch the mutual fund business – The Victory Funds. John went on to become sales manager for the fund family and ultimately sales manager for the institutional asset management business.

John subsequently joined Prudential Investments and was responsible for strategic account relationships across mutual funds, separately managed accounts, variable annuity and sub-advisory businesses. At Prudential, John went on to run retail distribution for Prudential’s mutual fund and SMA business, leading all aspects of the organization.

John was also President of Reich &Tang, at the time an investment affiliate of Natixis Global Asset Management. At Reich & Tang, John led the firm’s growth efforts -including sales, client management, marketing, product management and corporate development.

John is a graduate of Skidmore College with a B.S. in Business Administration and of Case Western Reserve University with an M.B.A. in Finance. He holds FINRA Series 7, 63, and 24.Greg Smith, CFAGreg Smith, CFASenior Managing Director of OperationsMr. Smith has over thirty years of experience in the financial services industry, developed through diverse responsibilities in executive management, sales & marketing, business & product development, investment management, operations and compliance. Prior to joining Horizon, Mr. Smith was the Managing Principal of Immersion Investment Group, a business consulting firm based in Charlotte, NC. Before starting Immersion, he was Vice President for TIAA-CREF Life Insurance Company, responsible for product and strategic business development as well as third-party investment research. Previously, Mr. Smith was President of Sunset Financial Services Inc. (SFS), an independent broker/dealer. Also during his career, Mr. Smith started and grew another retail Broker/Dealer, developed a personal book of business as a Financial Advisor, analyzed companies in a variety of industries for both traditional and asset-based lenders, and was interim Chief Investment Officer for a Registered Investment Advisor. Mr. Smith holds FINRA Series 7, 24, 53, 63 and 65, a Bachelor’s degree in Finance from The University of Notre Dame, and a MBA in International Management from The University of Texas at Dallas. He is also a Chartered Financial Analyst (CFA) and is currently a member of the CFA Institute & CFA Society North Carolina.Matt ChambersMatt ChambersGeneral Counsel and Chief Compliance OfficerPrior to joining Horizon, Mr. Chambers was an attorney with the law firm of Kilpatrick Townsend & Stockton, where he focused on representing investment advisers and mutual funds. He is a member of the National Society of Compliance Professionals, and is a regular speaker on investment management and compliance matters for NSCP and other industry groups.Mr. Chambers received his JD from University of Georgia School of Law, a Master of Arts degree from Gordon-Conwell Theological Seminary and a BA from The University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.Scott LadnerScott LadnerHead of InvestmentsMr. Ladner serves as Head of Investment Management and is the Chair of the Investment Committee for Horizon. In these capacities, he oversees all aspects of the Investment Management division for the firm.  He also provides the Investment Management division with Macro analysis and interpretation of global derivatives, credit, foreign exchange, equity, and funding markets.  His previous roles at Horizon included Head of Risk and Director of Quantitative & Alternative Strategies.Prior to Horizon, Mr. Ladner was a founder of Charlotte Global Advisors and Principal Guard, LLC. Mr. Ladner helped to launch an equity index volatility and dispersion trading unit at PEΔK6 Investments in Chicago, a proprietary listed option and volatility trading firm. Previously at First Union/Wachovia, Mr. Ladner founded and ran the $4 billion equity swap and forwards portfolio while also managing equity option and volatility portfolios. He also co-founded and managed the Risk Arbitrage and Special Situations portfolio. Mr. Ladner then managed the $300 billion notional swaption and cap/floor portion of the bank’s interest rate derivatives portfolio.Mr. Ladner received his BA in Economics and Russian Language & Literature from the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.SalesJosh BartholomewJosh BartholomewHead of ConsultingMr. Bartholomew is responsible for the firm’s Consulting efforts. In this capacity he works directly with investment advisors to help support their efforts in growing their practice. With his comprehensive view of advisory business, he can offer expert insights and actionable strategies to our advisor clients through a comprehensive suite of education, training and consulting solutions.

Prior to Horizon, Mr. Bartholomew was a regional account executive at Renaissance World Wide, Inc., a national consulting firm.

Mr. Bartholomew received a BA from North Carolina at Greensboro and a MS from Appalachian State University.James Tavares, AIFJames Tavares, AIFHead of Retirement Plan ServicesMr. Tavares is responsible for the Retirement Plan Services effort at Horizon. He focuses on empowering advisors to efficiently and profitably grow their retirement plan business by combining plan outcome-based investment expertise with innovative tools and services.

Prior to joining Horizon Investments in 2015, Mr. Tavares was an institutional retirement plan consultant for Natixis Global Asset Management, from 2010-2015. Prior to working with Natixis, James worked a number of investments and retirement planning roles for Fidelity Investments for 6 years.

Mr. Tavares majored in Business Economics at Brown University.
Eddie RollinsEddie RollinsHead of National AccountsMr. Rollins is charged with managing the strategic relationship effort of the firm. In this capacity he works directly with the home office executives of our distribution partners to ensure proper support and strategic alignment. Mr. Rollins joined Horizon in 2010 and brings three decades of financial service experience to his role.

Mr. Rollins is a graduate of Appalachian State University.Dan O’TooleDan O’TooleHead of National SalesMr. O’Toole manages the firm's national sales efforts with a focus on the development of relationships with financial advisors throughout the United States. Mr. O'Toole brings three decades of industry experience to his role.

Prior to joining Horizon in 2015, he served as a Senior Vice President with AssetMark Inc, as the Head of National Sales and Strategic Business Development for the $26 billion firm. During his tenure, Dan lead their approximately 100 person sales team, while overseeing the development of their strategic accounts relationships with Independent Broker-Dealers and most recently overseeing their large advisor relationships. As one of the senior leaders of AssetMark, since its inception in 1996, Dan has worked with thousands of advisors and institutions to help them grow their businesses and client relationships.

Mr. O'Toole holds a BA in Economics from San Diego State University. He also holds the FINRA Series 7, 66 and 26 licenses.


